William E. Thiele was named president of this insurance holding company, succeeding John H. Bretherick Jr., who plans to retire soon after turning 60 years old in December.
Mr. Thiele, 47, has been senior executive vice president in charge of the company's insurance operations.
He will also take the chief operating officer post of Continental, which had been vacant.
John P. Mascotte, 50, remains chairman and chief executive officer.
Mr. Bretherick will also retire from the board. 

